# JusticeFlow Case Management API Specification

**Document Version:** 1.0  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Project:** JusticeFlow Case Management (Grant #SCA-BACKLOG-2026-077)  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Scope:** This specification defines a RESTful API for scheduling and case management in county misdemeanor courts. The API tracks defendant profiles, court dates, assigned counsel, case status, and hearing outcomes to mitigate administrative backlog and reduce missed appearances. It builds on Phase 2 workflow automation, integrating with existing court databases and notification systems.  

This API assumes deployment on a secure cloud infrastructure (e.g., AWS or Azure) with OAuth 2.0 authentication for court administrators, judges, and pretrial services personnel. All endpoints require role-based access control (RBAC): e.g., admins can create/update, clerks can read/update status. Data validation ensures no missed appearances by enforcing mandatory fields and automated reminders via integrated email/SMS gateways.

## 1. Data Models

Data models are defined using JSON Schema for clarity and implementation in a relational database (e.g., PostgreSQL) or NoSQL (e.g., MongoDB). Primary entities include DefendantProfile, CourtDate, AssignedCounsel, CaseStatus, and HearingOutcome. Relationships are enforced via foreign keys or references.

### DefendantProfile
Represents the defendant's basic information and case linkages.

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "defendantId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid", "description": "Unique identifier" },
    "fullName": { "type": "string", "minLength": 1, "maxLength": 100 },
    "dateOfBirth": { "type": "string", "format": "date" },
    "contactInfo": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "phone": { "type": "string", "pattern": "^\\+?[1-9]\\d{1,14}$" },
        "email": { "type": "string", "format": "email" },
        "address": { "type": "string", "maxLength": 200 }
      },
      "required": ["phone"]  // Ensures contact for reminders
    },
    "caseIds": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" } }
  },
  "required": ["defendantId", "fullName", "dateOfBirth", "contactInfo"]
}
```

### CourtDate
Tracks scheduled court appearances with backlog prevention flags (e.g., auto-reminder triggers).

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "dateId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" },
    "caseId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" },
    "defendantId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" },
    "scheduledDateTime": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
    "courtroom": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Courtroom1", "Courtroom2", "Courtroom3", "Courtroom4", "Courtroom5"] },  // Based on pilot courtrooms
    "type": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Arraignment", "Pretrial", "Hearing", "Sentencing"] },
    "reminderStatus": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Pending", "Sent", "Acknowledged"] },  // Integrates with notification system
    "notes": { "type": "string", "maxLength": 500 }
  },
  "required": ["dateId", "caseId", "defendantId", "scheduledDateTime", "courtroom", "type"]
}
```

### AssignedCounsel
Links attorneys or public defenders to cases.

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "counselId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" },
    "caseId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" },
    "attorneyName": { "type": "string", "minLength": 1, "maxLength": 100 },
    "barNumber": { "type": "string", "maxLength": 50 },
    "contactInfo": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "phone": { "type": "string", "pattern": "^\\+?[1-9]\\d{1,14}$" },
        "email": { "type": "string", "format": "email" }
      },
      "required": ["email"]
    },
    "assignmentDate": { "type": "string", "format": "date" }
  },
  "required": ["counselId", "caseId", "attorneyName", "barNumber", "contactInfo"]
}
```

### CaseStatus
Tracks the lifecycle of a misdemeanor case to prevent backlog stagnation.

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "caseId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" },
    "status": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Filed", "Pending", "InProgress", "Continued", "Disposed"] },
    "lastUpdated": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
    "backlogFlag": { "type": "boolean", "description": "True if case exceeds 30 days without update (auto-triggered)" },
    "notes": { "type": "string", "maxLength": 500 }
  },
  "required": ["caseId", "status", "lastUpdated"]
}
```

### HearingOutcome
Records outcomes to close loops and update statuses.

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "outcomeId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" },
    "dateId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" },
    "caseId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid" },
    "outcome": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Guilty", "NotGuilty", "Dismissed", "Continued", "NoShow"] },
    "sentenceDetails": { "type": "string", "maxLength": 500 },
    "recordedDate": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" }
  },
  "required": ["outcomeId", "dateId", "caseId", "outcome", "recordedDate"]
}
```

