# Technical Specification: Trauma-Informed Intake Schema for UnityPath Social Service Gateway

**Document ID:** MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-TIS-001  
**Version:** 1.0  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Project Phase:** Eligibility Engine Modernization (Phase 2)  
**Approval Status:** Pending Client Review (Assumes alignment with DHS policy on trauma-informed practices, as pre-approved in program scope)  

## Overview
This specification outlines a trauma-informed intake schema extension for the UnityPath Social Service Gateway. The schema enables applicants to self-report barriers including housing instability, health concerns, and domestic trauma. Design principles prioritize sensitivity, optionality, and minimal intrusion:
- All barrier-related fields are optional to avoid re-traumatization.
- Language in field labels and descriptions uses neutral, empowering terminology (e.g., "challenges" instead of "problems").
- Data is structured for automated prioritization and routing: Urgent flags trigger immediate caseworker alerts and resource referrals (e.g., via integration with emergency housing APIs).
- Integration ensures data flows to the eligibility engine for needs-based prioritization without requiring full disclosure.

This extends the existing intake model (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-BASE-v2.1) and complies with client policies on data privacy (e.g., HIPAA for health data, FERPA where applicable).

## Data Model
The intake schema is defined using JSON Schema (Draft 2020-12) for compatibility with the gateway's RESTful API and database (PostgreSQL backend). It includes a new `barriers` object within the applicant profile. Validation ensures data integrity while allowing partial submissions.

### JSON Schema Definition
```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://unitypath.dhs.gov/schemas/intake-trauma-informed-v1.0.json",
  "title": "Trauma-Informed Intake Schema",
  "description": "Schema for self-reporting barriers in social service applications.",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "applicantId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier for the applicant (auto-generated on submission).",
      "format": "uuid"
    },
    "submissionTimestamp": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "ISO 8601 timestamp of submission.",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "basicDemographics": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Existing demographics from base schema (ref: BASE-v2.1).",
      "properties": { /* Omitted for brevity; extends existing model */ }
    },
    "barriers": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Optional self-reported barriers. All fields are voluntary.",
      "properties": {
        "housingInstability": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "isExperiencing": {
              "type": "boolean",
              "description": "Indicate if you are facing housing challenges (optional)."
            },
            "details": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Optional description (e.g., eviction risk, homelessness). Max 500 chars.",
              "maxLength": 500
            },
            "urgencyLevel": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": ["low", "medium", "high"],
              "description": "Self-assessed urgency (triggers routing if 'high')."
            }
          }
        },
        "healthConcerns": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "isExperiencing": {
              "type": "boolean",
              "description": "Indicate if you have health-related challenges (optional)."
            },
            "details": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Optional description (e.g., chronic illness, mental health). Max 500 chars. Note: Protected under HIPAA.",
              "maxLength": 500
            },
            "urgencyLevel": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": ["low", "medium", "high"],
              "description": "Self-assessed urgency (triggers health resource routing if 'high')."
            }
          }
        },
        "domesticTrauma": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "isExperiencing": {
              "type": "boolean",
              "description": "Indicate if you are facing relationship or family challenges (optional)."
            },
            "details": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Optional description (e.g., domestic violence, family separation). Max 500 chars. Confidential and protected.",
              "maxLength": 500
            },
            "urgencyLevel": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": ["low", "medium", "high"],
              "description": "Self-assessed urgency (triggers immediate safety referrals if 'high')."
            }
          }
        },
        "otherBarriers": {
          "type": "array",
          "description": "Additional self-reported barriers.",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "type": { "type": "string", "description": "e.g., 'financial', 'transportation'" },
              "details": { "type": "string", "maxLength": 500 },
              "urgencyLevel": { "type": "string", "enum": ["low", "medium", "high"] }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "consent": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "description": "Applicant consent for data sharing with caseworkers/resources (required if barriers are reported)."
    }
  },
  "required": ["applicantId", "submissionTimestamp", "consent"]
}
```

### Data Validation Rules
- **Optionality:** Barriers object is optional; if present, sub-fields default to null if not provided.
- **Urgency Flagging:** If any `urgencyLevel` is "high", auto-set a system flag `urgentRoutingRequired: true` in the database.
- **Privacy Controls:** Health and domestic trauma details are encrypted at rest (AES-256) and access-restricted to authorized caseworkers via role-based access control (RBAC).

## API Contracts
The schema integrates with the existing UnityPath API. New endpoints handle submission and querying.

### Endpoint: Submit Intake
- **Method:** POST  
- **Path:** `/api/v1/intake/submit`  
- **Request Body:** JSON conforming to the schema above.  
- **Headers:**  
  - `Authorization: Bearer [JWT Token]` (Applicant or proxy authentication).  
  - `Content-Type: application/json`  
- **Response:**  
  - 201 Created: `{ "status": "submitted", "applicationId": "uuid", "nextSteps": "Caseworker review pending" }`  
  - 400 Bad Request: Validation errors (e.g., missing consent).  
- **Rate Limiting:** 5 requests per minute per IP to prevent abuse.

