# Technical Specification: Household Stability Protocol Integration for UnityPath Social Service Gateway

**Document ID:** MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-HSP-001  
**Version:** 1.0  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Project Phase:** Eligibility Engine Modernization (Phase 2)  
**Approval Status:** Pending Client Review (Assumes alignment with DHS policy on household assessments, inter-agency data sharing, and child welfare protocols, as pre-approved in program scope)  

## Overview
This specification defines the Household Stability Protocol as an extension to the UnityPath Social Service Gateway. The protocol automates escalation based on trends in the Stability Score (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-SPT-001 and MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-SSI-001). If an applicant's score fails to improve over successive review cycles (configurable, default: 3 consecutive months with no increase >= 10 points), the system triggers a comprehensive home assessment and shares a behavioral case summary with the Child and Family Services (CFS) interface for evaluation against agency care standards.

Key design principles:
- Automation is driven by a scheduled backend job (e.g., monthly review cycle) analyzing `scoreHistory` trends.
- "Improvement" is defined as a score increase of at least a configurable delta (default: 10 points) from the previous cycle.
- Triggers include scheduling a home assessment via integration with the agency's assessment management system and secure data sharing with CFS via API.
- The behavioral case summary is a synthesized report aggregating data from barriers (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-TIS-001), progress metrics, and disbursement history, anonymized where required.
- Compliance: Data sharing adheres to inter-agency agreements (e.g., encrypted transmission, consent verification, audit logging). Escalations include caseworker notifications for oversight.
- This integrates with existing applicant profiles, adding a `householdStability` object for protocol tracking.
- Fallback: Manual override available for caseworkers to cancel or expedite triggers.

The protocol supports capacity management by prioritizing high-risk households for intervention.

## Data Model
The Household Stability Protocol extends the applicant profile with a `householdStability` object, including trend analysis, trigger status, and summary generation logic. Data is stored in the PostgreSQL backend, with historical trends computed on-demand or via scheduled jobs.

### JSON Schema Extension
This modularly extends the progress tracker and disbursement schemas (ref: https://unitypath.dhs.gov/schemas/intake-progress-tracker-v1.0.json and https://unitypath.dhs.gov/schemas/disbursement-integration-v1.0.json).

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://unitypath.dhs.gov/schemas/household-stability-protocol-v1.0.json",
  "title": "Household Stability Protocol Extension",
  "description": "Extension for monitoring score trends and triggering assessments/data sharing.",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "applicantId": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "uuid",
      "description": "Reference to applicant from base schema."
    },
    "householdStability": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Tracks protocol status and triggers.",
      "properties": {
        "reviewCycles": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Number of consecutive cycles to evaluate (default: 3).",
          "minimum": 1,
          "default": 3
        },
        "improvementDelta": {
          "type": "number",
          "description": "Minimum score increase required to reset cycle count (default: 10).",
          "minimum": 0,
          "default": 10
        },
        "trendStatus": {
          "type": "string",
          "enum": ["improving", "stable", "declining", "escalated"],
          "description": "Computed status based on scoreHistory analysis."
        },
        "escalationTriggers": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "homeAssessment": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {
                "triggered": { "type": "boolean", "default": false },
                "assessmentId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid", "description": "ID of scheduled assessment." },
                "scheduledDate": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" }
              }
            },
            "cfsSharing": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {
                "triggered": { "type": "boolean", "default": false },
                "summaryId": { "type": "string", "format": "uuid", "description": "ID of shared behavioral case summary." },
                "sharedDate": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "behavioralCaseSummary": {
          "type": "object",
          "description": "Synthesized summary for CFS sharing (generated on trigger).",
          "properties": {
            "summaryContent": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Aggregated report (e.g., JSON or PDF blob reference). Includes barriers, metrics, score trends. Max 10KB.",
              "maxLength": 10240
            },
            "generationDate": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" }
          }
        },
        "protocolHistory": {
          "type": "array",
          "description": "Log of protocol evaluations.",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "cycleDate": { "type": "string", "format": "date" },
              "scoreAtCycle": { "type": "number", "minimum": 0, "maximum": 100 },
              "actionTaken": { "type": "string", "description": "e.g., 'monitored', 'escalated'" }
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "required": ["reviewCycles", "improvementDelta", "trendStatus", "escalationTriggers"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["applicantId", "householdStability"]
}
```

### Data Validation and Computation Rules
- **Trend Analysis:** Monthly job (e.g., first of the month) queries `scoreHistory` for the last `reviewCycles` entries. If no improvement (>= `improvementDelta`) in each consecutive pair, set `trendStatus` to "declining" and trigger escalations if cycles are met.
- **Summary Generation:** On trigger, aggregate data into `behavioralCaseSummary` (e.g., via template engine like Handlebars or backend service). Include anonymized details from barriers, metrics, and history.
- **Triggers:** Set `triggered: true`, generate IDs, and initiate integrations (e.g., schedule assessment, share summary).
- **Reset Logic:** If improvement detected, reset cycle counter and set `trendStatus` to "improving".
