# Technical Specification: Conditional Recovery API for UnityPath Social Service Gateway

**Document ID:** MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-CRA-001  
**Version:** 1.0  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Project Phase:** Eligibility Engine Modernization (Phase 2)  
**Approval Status:** Pending Client Review (Assumes alignment with DHS policy on conditional benefits activation, third-party monitoring integrations, and real-time verification protocols, as pre-approved in program scope)  

## Overview
This specification defines the Conditional Recovery API as an extension to the UnityPath Social Service Gateway. It targets applicants in the lowest stability tier (configurable, default: Stability Score < 30, ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-SPT-001). Benefit activation requires real-time verification of treatment attendance, supervised-program participation, or medication adherence via integration with a contracted third-party monitoring platform (e.g., a secure API from a vendor like HealthMonitor Inc. or similar).

Key design principles:
- Verification is real-time, polled or pushed from the third-party platform during disbursement requests.
- Full disbursement is gated: Partial or withheld until verification passes (e.g., 80% adherence threshold met in the current cycle).
- Integration uses secure APIs (e.g., OAuth2 for authentication, HTTPS for data exchange) to fetch adherence data.
- This builds on existing disbursement logic (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-SSI-001) and household stability protocols (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-HSP-001), adding a `conditionalRecovery` object to applicant records.
- Compliance: Verifications are consent-based, with audit logging for all checks. Data from third-party is encrypted in transit and at rest (AES-256). Fallback to manual verification if API fails.
- Tier Determination: Automatically assessed from `stabilityScore`; escalates to this API only for lowest tier applicants.
- Configurable thresholds (e.g., adherence rate, verification types) allow for policy adjustments.

The API supports automated workflows, such as notifications to applicants for pending verifications and alerts to caseworkers for failures.

## Data Model
The Conditional Recovery API extends the applicant profile with a `conditionalRecovery` object, tracking verification requirements, status, and history. Data is stored in the PostgreSQL backend, with real-time updates via API integrations.

### JSON Schema Extension
This modularly extends the disbursement integration schema (ref: https://unitypath.dhs.gov/schemas/disbursement-integration-v1.0.json) and household stability schema.

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://unitypath.dhs.gov/schemas/conditional-recovery-v1.0.json",
  "title": "Conditional Recovery API Extension",
  "description": "Extension for real-time verification gating of benefits disbursement in low-stability tiers.",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "applicantId": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "uuid",
      "description": "Reference to applicant from base schema."
    },
    "conditionalRecovery": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Manages verification for lowest stability tier applicants.",
      "properties": {
        "stabilityTier": {
          "type": "string",
          "enum": ["low", "medium", "high"],
          "description": "Derived from stabilityScore (e.g., <30 = 'low')."
        },
        "verificationRequirements": {
          "type": "array",
          "description": "Required verifications (configurable per applicant).",
          "items": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": ["treatmentAttendance", "supervisedProgramParticipation", "medicationAdherence"]
          },
          "minItems": 1
        },
        "adherenceThreshold": {
          "type": "number",
          "description": "Minimum adherence rate for pass (default: 80%).",
          "minimum": 0,
          "maximum": 100,
          "default": 80
        },
        "thirdPartyProvider": {
          "type": "object",
          "description": "Details for contracted monitoring platform.",
          "properties": {
            "providerId": { "type": "string", "description": "e.g., 'HealthMonitorInc'" },
            "apiEndpoint": { "type": "string", "format": "uri", "description": "Base URL for verification API." },
            "authToken": { "type": "string", "description": "Secure token reference (stored encrypted)." }
          },
          "required": ["providerId", "apiEndpoint"]
        },
        "verificationStatus": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "status": { "type": "string", "enum": ["pending", "verified", "failed", "manualOverride"] },
            "lastChecked": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
            "adherenceRate": { "type": "number", "minimum": 0, "maximum": 100 },
            "details": { "type": "string", "description": "Verification response summary (e.g., 'Attendance: 85%').", "maxLength": 500 }
          }
        },
        "verificationHistory": {
          "type": "array",
          "description": "Log of past verifications.",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "date": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
              "type": { "type": "string", "enum": ["treatmentAttendance", "supervisedProgramParticipation", "medicationAdherence"] },
              "result": { "type": "string", "enum": ["pass", "fail"] },
              "adherenceRate": { "type": "number" }
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "required": ["stabilityTier", "verificationRequirements", "adherenceThreshold", "thirdPartyProvider", "verificationStatus"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["applicantId", "conditionalRecovery"]
}
```

### Data Validation and Computation Rules
- **Tier Assignment:** On score update, set `stabilityTier` (e.g., <30: "low", 30-60: "medium", >60: "high"). Only "low" activates conditional logic.
- **Verification Logic:** During disbursement, query third-party API for each required type. Compute aggregate `adherenceRate` (average if multiple). If >= `adherenceThreshold`, set `status: "verified"` and release full benefits; else, "failed" and withhold/partial release (configurable).
- **Real-Time Integration:** Use synchronous API calls (timeout: 10s) or webhooks for push notifications from the third-party.
- **Audit and Fallback:** Log all verifications immutably. If API fails, set `status: "pending"` and notify caseworker for manual review.
- **Data Retention:** History retained for 12 months; configurable.

